cs.AR, cs.PF, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.ET

This paper deals with power management in many-core systems, which involves optimization and control of system components such as cores and memory. This topic falls under the category of computer systems and architecture (cs.AR), as well as performance analysis and optimization (cs.PF) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of queuing models and optimization algorithms, which are relevant to the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and emerging technologies (cs.ET).
